I should be saying sorry.

00:14:44.888 --> 00:14:46.190
Oh, no. Not at all.

00:14:46.256 --> 00:14:48.425
One wouldn't expect
a marriage registration, right?

00:14:48.993 --> 00:14:49.927
Must’ve shocked you.

00:14:50.694 --> 00:14:52.363
Yeah, quite a bit.

00:14:52.429 --> 00:14:55.232
As you saw, I'm gay.

00:15:00.070 --> 00:15:01.538
Don't worry.

00:15:02.306 --> 00:15:03.507
About what?

00:15:05.542 --> 00:15:08.645
I'm the same as well.

00:15:09.413 --> 00:15:11.815
Oh, really? Oh, I see.

00:15:11.882 --> 00:15:13.817
But no need to worry about it.

00:15:13.884 --> 00:15:16.153
I’m not really hiding it.

00:15:16.887 --> 00:15:18.188
Is that so?

00:15:18.255 --> 00:15:21.925
I'm not exactly open about it,
but if people ask, I'd tell them.

00:15:24.795 --> 00:15:28.065
Even so, it’s not easy
to throw away that paper.

00:15:28.132 --> 00:15:29.867
Yeah.

00:15:29.933 --> 00:15:33.437
I had a hard time throwing it away myself.
I'm glad you did it for me.

00:15:35.339 --> 00:15:36.573
Wasn’t that also something

00:15:37.307 --> 00:15:39.076
similar to those reservation slips,

00:15:39.143 --> 00:15:41.812
and you looked forward to it?

00:15:42.913 --> 00:15:46.083
Not really. It didn’t mean anything.

00:15:46.150 --> 00:15:48.452
We can’t submit it anyway. It's pointless.

00:15:50.354 --> 00:15:51.188
Pointless?

00:15:51.755 --> 00:15:54.458
We can't get married anyway.
There's no point.

00:15:57.761 --> 00:15:58.862
You know,

00:15:59.797 --> 00:16:01.732
I went to a marriage consultation agency
the other day.

00:16:01.799 --> 00:16:02.699
Even though you can't marry?

00:16:02.766 --> 00:16:05.302
Yeah, but…

00:16:05.869 --> 00:16:07.137
there’s one for people like us.

00:16:08.338 --> 00:16:09.573
I went out of curiosity.

00:16:09.640 --> 00:16:12.509
Felt kind of excited, honestly.

00:16:13.544 --> 00:16:16.313
But every profile photo

00:16:16.380 --> 00:16:18.215
was pixelated.

00:16:18.949 --> 00:16:20.984
Total privacy protection.

00:16:21.552 --> 00:16:23.420
Which is nice, of course.

00:16:25.055 --> 00:16:25.923
But it felt like…

00:16:27.357 --> 00:16:29.726
in the end, people like us
are something to be censored.

00:16:30.294 --> 00:16:32.729
Hidden. That's just how

00:16:34.264 --> 00:16:36.133
we're forced to live our lives, I guess.

00:16:38.836 --> 00:16:40.938
Well, what I'm trying to say

00:16:41.905 --> 00:16:42.840
is, um…

00:16:45.342 --> 00:16:46.610
What are we supposed to do?

00:16:46.677 --> 00:16:49.713
Let's just drop this discussion.
It's pointless.

00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:51.381
Well then.

00:17:06.063 --> 00:17:08.065
You’ve got three hair swirls.

00:17:08.132 --> 00:17:09.366
No way!

00:17:09.433 --> 00:17:10.267
Aren't there five?

00:17:10.334 --> 00:17:12.069
You can't see it yourself, right?

00:17:12.136 --> 00:17:13.203
Hurry and take a picture.

00:17:13.270 --> 00:17:14.171
Okay.

00:17:16.340 --> 00:17:17.307
Here you go.

00:17:17.808 --> 00:17:18.642
Thanks.

00:17:18.709 --> 00:17:20.777
You can see it clearly.

00:17:21.678 --> 00:17:23.747
Hey, what's the meaning of this?

00:17:23.814 --> 00:17:25.082
Your hair swirl is beautiful!

00:17:25.149 --> 00:17:26.049
It is!

00:17:26.116 --> 00:17:27.784
Do you want anything?

00:17:28.919 --> 00:17:32.322
You were collecting coins yesterday,
weren’t you? Anything you want?

00:17:32.389 --> 00:17:35.492
I work with a group called Nikomado.

00:17:35.559 --> 00:17:38.162
We listen to people’s problems,
help them out--

00:17:38.228 --> 00:17:39.596
You're being a creep!

00:17:40.797 --> 00:17:42.966
You see,
I just want to have a talk with you.

00:17:43.033 --> 00:17:43.867
Get lost!

00:17:44.535 --> 00:17:46.136
-No, wait!
-We said get lost!

00:17:46.203 --> 00:17:47.538
Go away!

00:17:47.604 --> 00:17:50.073
-Let go of me!
-Get out of here!

00:17:55.612 --> 00:17:58.382
She refused to give us
her parents’ contact information.

00:17:58.448 --> 00:18:01.885
The only number
she finally gave us was yours.

00:18:02.786 --> 00:18:04.621
I'm really sorry about this.

00:18:04.688 --> 00:18:06.890
Please wait here.

00:18:06.957 --> 00:18:08.125
Can't you contact them?

00:18:08.192 --> 00:18:11.595
Like I said, both my mom and dad
are very nice people.

00:18:11.662 --> 00:18:13.730
They really care about me, and that’s why

00:18:13.797 --> 00:18:15.232
I don’t want to call them.

00:18:15.832 --> 00:18:17.634
I don’t want to bother them
during their trip.

00:18:18.902 --> 00:18:20.704
They'll be back tomorrow.

00:18:20.771 --> 00:18:21.939
I'm totally fine.

00:18:24.908 --> 00:18:26.043
Please come in.

00:18:26.109 --> 00:18:27.277
Please excuse me.

00:18:35.886 --> 00:18:37.487
I'm sorry.

00:18:38.922 --> 00:18:41.992
What time does your dad usually come home?

00:18:43.393 --> 00:18:44.428
It varies.

00:18:44.494 --> 00:18:47.130
-What about this Monday?
-What?

00:18:47.698 --> 00:18:50.867
For the parent-teacher meeting,
I’ll come to your house.

00:18:52.269 --> 00:18:53.370
Monday's not good…

00:18:53.437 --> 00:18:55.772
Then what about Tuesday or Wednesday?

00:18:56.773 --> 00:18:58.041
I'm not sure.

00:18:58.108 --> 00:19:01.211
How about Saturday then?
Maybe around 5:30 p.m.

00:19:05.549 --> 00:19:06.950
Okay.

00:19:11.221 --> 00:19:13.924
Good boy… Wait up!

00:19:14.992 --> 00:19:15.892
Oh, good evening.

00:19:16.526 --> 00:19:17.861
What are you doing?

00:19:17.928 --> 00:19:20.897
Figured I'd bathe them,
given how huge the yard is.

00:19:21.965 --> 00:19:22.966
Huh?

00:19:24.534 --> 00:19:26.169
Rearranging stuff again?

00:19:26.236 --> 00:19:27.704
Yeah, something like that.

00:19:29.139 --> 00:19:30.841
Good boy…

00:19:35.979 --> 00:19:37.681
Is this yours too, Mr. Hatano?

00:19:38.849 --> 00:19:42.352
Yeah, I just started keeping it recently.

00:19:42.419 --> 00:19:44.988
What's its name?

00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:48.258
-Good question.
-Huh?

00:19:48.892 --> 00:19:51.495
It was abandoned. Like these two.

00:20:20.290 --> 00:20:21.792
Oh! Let's go.

00:20:31.802 --> 00:20:33.470
NO JUNK MAIL, PLEASE

00:20:34.671 --> 00:20:36.406
-Hey, you!
-Yes?

00:20:36.473 --> 00:20:37.574
You put something in, yes?

00:20:37.641 --> 00:20:38.475
What?

00:20:39.042 --> 00:20:40.410
Look what's written here.

00:20:40.477 --> 00:20:43.246
-No, I… It's not--
-Take it back.

00:20:43.313 --> 00:20:45.215
-But…
-See?

00:20:46.383 --> 00:20:48.452
Huh?

00:20:48.518 --> 00:20:51.154
-Um…
-What's the meaning of this?

00:20:54.224 --> 00:20:55.992
You always liked strawberries, right?

00:20:56.059 --> 00:20:58.195
No. You must be confusing me
with your new daughter.

00:21:00.664 --> 00:21:03.367
Come on. Don't say that.

00:21:05.702 --> 00:21:07.437
So, what did you want to talk about today?

00:21:09.606 --> 00:21:10.574
I've got a favor to ask.

00:21:11.308 --> 00:21:12.676
Did Mom call you?

00:21:12.743 --> 00:21:13.777
It's not that.

00:21:14.411 --> 00:21:15.579
Then, what is it?

00:21:16.413 --> 00:21:17.714
There’s a parent-teacher meeting.

00:21:18.448 --> 00:21:19.316
What?

00:21:20.417 --> 00:21:21.251
So,

00:21:21.785 --> 00:21:23.487
I want you to come.

00:21:23.553 --> 00:21:26.790
Me? But I don’t know anything. No way.

00:21:26.857 --> 00:21:28.558
Just bluff your way through.

00:21:28.625 --> 00:21:30.494
There's no way I'm going to pull it off.

00:21:34.364 --> 00:21:36.933
Right. You’ve got your new family
to worry about, Mr. Ichigaya.

00:21:37.501 --> 00:21:40.537
Come on. Don’t be like that.

00:21:41.805 --> 00:21:44.741
Welcome! This way, please.

00:21:47.577 --> 00:21:50.180
Two guys coming to eat crepes?

00:21:51.915 --> 00:21:55.152
He loved these banana crepes.

00:21:56.586 --> 00:22:00.056
Can’t believe it ended up under a bench.
So, why’d you bring this?

00:22:00.657 --> 00:22:01.658
What do you want?

00:22:04.728 --> 00:22:07.297
I'm… the same kind.

00:22:08.131 --> 00:22:09.232
Sorry, what?

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:12.502
I'm saying I’m gay too.

00:22:13.937 --> 00:22:15.138
Did he say "gay"?

00:22:16.206 --> 00:22:17.741
Phew.

00:22:17.808 --> 00:22:19.643
Here I thought you were here
to blackmail me.

00:22:19.709 --> 00:22:21.178
Oh, no.

00:22:21.711 --> 00:22:24.481
I just couldn’t bring myself
to throw it away.

00:22:26.283 --> 00:22:29.453
Sakuta said that this form was pointless.

00:22:29.519 --> 00:22:31.655
MARRIAGE REGISTRATION FORM

00:22:31.721 --> 00:22:33.690
Did something happen between you two?

