00:30:12.815 --> 00:30:18.021
No home, oh, no home

00:30:19.222 --> 00:30:24.427
The vast sky is your roof

00:30:25.161 --> 00:30:26.663
The day after tomorrow…

00:30:26.729 --> 00:30:29.465
I wonder if Hatano didn't have a home.

00:30:31.834 --> 00:30:33.369
Poor man.

00:30:34.370 --> 00:30:36.773
Your new home

00:30:38.041 --> 00:30:42.912
No home, oh, no home

00:30:43.646 --> 00:30:48.818
The vast sky is your roof

00:30:49.519 --> 00:30:54.424
The day after tomorrow
The day after tomo--

00:30:57.193 --> 00:30:58.728
I can hear it from all the way up.

00:30:58.795 --> 00:31:00.463
Oh, my bad.

00:31:00.530 --> 00:31:02.198
-What’s that song?
-Huh?

00:31:02.265 --> 00:31:03.232
The title of that song.

00:31:04.434 --> 00:31:06.769
I don't know. Maybe "No Home"?

00:31:09.339 --> 00:31:10.373
Um…

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:11.274
Yes?

00:31:12.008 --> 00:31:14.544
On Saturday, around 5:30 p.m.
in the evening, will you be home?

00:31:15.144 --> 00:31:17.647
Yeah, I get off work
and come back by then. Why?

00:31:20.350 --> 00:31:21.351
Well…

00:31:23.152 --> 00:31:25.288
I want to see your parakeet.

00:31:26.289 --> 00:31:27.123
My parakeet?

00:31:27.690 --> 00:31:28.524
Yes.

00:31:29.492 --> 00:31:31.060
Then, it's settled.

00:31:38.701 --> 00:31:39.535
HIBINO REAL ESTATE CO., LTD.

00:31:39.602 --> 00:31:41.604
No home…

00:31:53.816 --> 00:31:55.184
Hello.

00:31:56.986 --> 00:31:58.021
Hello.

00:31:58.087 --> 00:31:59.956
You're always here, huh?

00:32:00.023 --> 00:32:01.457
Sakuta.

00:32:01.524 --> 00:32:02.492
Yes?

00:32:02.558 --> 00:32:03.393
Uh…

00:32:09.365 --> 00:32:11.234
What do you think about buying a house?

00:32:11.968 --> 00:32:13.102
What?

00:32:13.169 --> 00:32:14.003
Here.

00:32:15.638 --> 00:32:16.472
Please take it.

00:32:22.211 --> 00:32:23.212
INTRODUCING PAIR LOANS

00:32:23.780 --> 00:32:25.748
Wait. What is all this supposed to mean?

00:32:26.349 --> 00:32:28.785
Living out of your car seems tough.

00:32:29.352 --> 00:32:30.920
Well, that's true, but…

00:32:30.987 --> 00:32:33.289
-I've spoken to Yoshida as well.
-What?

00:32:33.356 --> 00:32:34.557
I've heard the circumstances.

00:32:34.624 --> 00:32:36.926
Huh? You went and met him?

00:32:36.993 --> 00:32:39.395
Well, sort of… yeah.

00:32:40.963 --> 00:32:43.566
You may not be able to file
for the marriage registration now,

00:32:43.633 --> 00:32:45.568
but maybe buying a house

00:32:45.635 --> 00:32:47.437
could be the "clamp" instead.

00:32:48.404 --> 00:32:50.740
Then, when breakup talk comes up,
dealing with the mortgage,

00:32:50.807 --> 00:32:53.109
house rights, taxes, etc.…

00:32:53.176 --> 00:32:55.645
Figuring out how to divide things
becomes such a hassle

00:32:55.711 --> 00:32:58.047
that you just give up on breaking up,

00:32:58.114 --> 00:33:00.149
and that way, you and Yoshida

00:33:00.216 --> 00:33:03.186
could then stay together.

00:33:04.353 --> 00:33:06.089
Just being gay makes love meaningless.

00:33:06.155 --> 00:33:07.824
You don’t seriously believe that, right?

00:33:07.890 --> 00:33:10.293
If so, then just like how you, Sakuta,

00:33:10.359 --> 00:33:12.862
create meaning by working hard
on your reservation slips,

00:33:12.929 --> 00:33:15.531
we can create meaning for ourselves.

00:33:16.099 --> 00:33:19.502
"Man was born for love and revolution."

00:33:20.269 --> 00:33:22.205
That was what Dazai said.

00:33:23.406 --> 00:33:25.475
So, let’s buy a house, make it our clamp,

00:33:25.541 --> 00:33:28.945
and prove our love has meaning too!

00:33:29.011 --> 00:33:32.482
That will be our love and revolution!

00:33:34.283 --> 00:33:35.118
Don't you agree?

00:33:37.186 --> 00:33:38.254
Sakuta.

00:33:39.455 --> 00:33:42.158
-Um…
-Could you not come any closer?

00:33:43.059 --> 00:33:45.094
You're scaring me, to say the least.

00:33:45.661 --> 00:33:46.496
Scary?

00:33:46.562 --> 00:33:49.332
You met my ex, looked
at my marriage registration form,

00:33:49.398 --> 00:33:51.200
and the nonsense about houses and clamps.

00:33:51.267 --> 00:33:52.468
Like, what are you on about?

00:33:52.535 --> 00:33:54.937
That's some freaky stuff you're doing.

00:33:55.004 --> 00:33:58.441
Keep this up, and you’ll probably
get arrested one day.

00:33:58.508 --> 00:33:59.642
What?

00:33:59.709 --> 00:34:02.812
Love and revolution, whatever.

00:34:02.879 --> 00:34:04.914
Do as you like.

00:34:04.981 --> 00:34:05.882
Bye.

00:34:13.122 --> 00:34:15.124
I'm such a fool…

00:34:17.894 --> 00:34:19.061
Coming.

00:34:20.129 --> 00:34:20.963
Oh.

00:34:21.564 --> 00:34:23.799
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:34:23.866 --> 00:34:25.668
Right. The parakeet, yes? One sec--

00:34:26.168 --> 00:34:27.003
I'll be back later.

00:34:33.910 --> 00:34:35.011
Coming.

00:34:40.750 --> 00:34:41.684
This is my dad.

00:34:41.751 --> 00:34:43.319
-Huh?
-What?

00:34:43.386 --> 00:34:44.620
What's wrong?

00:34:45.188 --> 00:34:46.756
You're her father?

00:34:47.623 --> 00:34:48.457
Uh, n--

00:34:48.524 --> 00:34:49.759
Yes, he's my dad!

00:34:49.825 --> 00:34:51.427
-Your dad, Hotaru?
-Yes. My dad.

00:34:51.994 --> 00:34:54.597
And this is my homeroom teacher,
Mr. Sakuta.

00:34:56.832 --> 00:34:58.000
What's going on?

00:35:03.539 --> 00:35:05.608
What a small world we live in.

00:35:07.009 --> 00:35:08.277
Are you two friends?

00:35:08.344 --> 00:35:09.579
Not at all.

00:35:10.780 --> 00:35:12.181
‎I see.

00:35:13.716 --> 00:35:17.386
Today I came by to check in
about your daughter.

00:35:17.453 --> 00:35:19.355
-Daughter?
-I'm his daughter. Right, Dad?

00:35:20.690 --> 00:35:22.959
-May I come in?
-Oh, sure!

00:35:23.025 --> 00:35:24.527
-Huh?
-Come on in.

00:35:24.594 --> 00:35:26.062
Hey!

00:35:26.128 --> 00:35:28.164
-Please excuse me.
-Ah, right.

00:35:31.734 --> 00:35:32.735
Dad.

00:35:34.570 --> 00:35:36.005
-Dad!
-Yes?

00:35:36.072 --> 00:35:37.506
Offer him some tea.

00:35:38.975 --> 00:35:41.911
-Please don’t trouble yourself.
-But I should…

00:35:41.978 --> 00:35:44.013
Really, no need. I’m fine.

00:35:45.514 --> 00:35:46.349
Okay.

00:35:49.652 --> 00:35:52.054
Once again, I’m Sakuta,
her homeroom teacher.

00:35:53.356 --> 00:35:54.390
I'm Hatano.

00:35:54.457 --> 00:35:56.892
With Hotaru’s future path
needing to be decided soon,

00:35:56.959 --> 00:36:00.696
I wanted to meet you and discuss it
together. That’s why I came today.

00:36:01.831 --> 00:36:02.832
First and foremost,

00:36:03.899 --> 00:36:06.335
about going on to high school…

00:36:06.402 --> 00:36:08.571
Shall I assume she plans to do so?

00:36:10.906 --> 00:36:12.441
I’m still thinking about it.

00:36:13.042 --> 00:36:15.578
Personally, if you don’t have
a clear idea of your future

00:36:15.645 --> 00:36:17.680
or what you want to do yet,

00:36:17.747 --> 00:36:20.049
it’s better to move forward
with high school.

00:36:21.050 --> 00:36:23.886
Right now, Kusunoki's grades are…

00:36:23.953 --> 00:36:25.154
No! Shoo!

00:36:25.221 --> 00:36:26.922
Bad boy! Shoo!

00:36:28.057 --> 00:36:29.091
Sorry about that.

00:36:29.925 --> 00:36:33.663
If she pushes just a little harder,
referrals and more choices will open up.

00:36:35.131 --> 00:36:37.667
Do you have any idea
what kind of high school you’d like?

00:36:38.234 --> 00:36:39.568
It’s best to decide early.

00:36:39.635 --> 00:36:41.637
Okay. I’ll think about it.

00:36:45.474 --> 00:36:47.777
And what about you, as her father?

00:36:51.747 --> 00:36:53.883
He’s still thinking it over too.
Right, Dad?

00:36:55.951 --> 00:36:56.952
Yes…

00:36:58.688 --> 00:37:02.024
I said stop that! Go, shoo!

00:37:03.359 --> 00:37:04.393
Sorry about that.

00:37:08.230 --> 00:37:11.167
Could I speak with your father
alone for a bit?

00:37:11.667 --> 00:37:12.902
-What?
-Huh?

00:37:21.644 --> 00:37:22.745
About Hotaru…

00:37:23.512 --> 00:37:25.281
How is she like at home?

00:37:28.617 --> 00:37:30.386
She was taken into custody
in Toyoko the other day.

00:37:30.986 --> 00:37:32.321
Have you heard about it?

00:37:35.157 --> 00:37:36.492
‎Um…

00:37:37.693 --> 00:37:38.794
Could I get a reply?

00:37:40.329 --> 00:37:42.965
-Yes.
-With the incident and all, life is hard.

00:37:43.032 --> 00:37:44.533
What?

00:37:44.600 --> 00:37:47.169
Whatever the circumstances, please…

00:37:47.737 --> 00:37:49.805
Please make Hotaru your top priority.

00:37:52.241 --> 00:37:53.976
This is a crucial stage for her.

00:37:54.043 --> 00:37:55.444
Her third year of middle school.

00:37:56.178 --> 00:37:57.880
Buying a house, clamps,

00:37:58.681 --> 00:37:59.749
and what else was it?

00:38:00.916 --> 00:38:01.984
Love and revolution?

00:38:02.051 --> 00:38:05.087
If you’ve got time to poke your nose
in my affairs--

00:38:06.288 --> 00:38:08.290
I’ll go buy some tea.

00:38:09.258 --> 00:38:10.092
What?

00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:12.428
Hey!

00:38:14.697 --> 00:38:15.865
Hey!

00:38:16.832 --> 00:38:17.900
What's going on?

00:38:17.967 --> 00:38:19.435
Please play along.

00:38:20.836 --> 00:38:21.804
I'm begging you.

00:38:27.209 --> 00:38:28.611
‎HIBINO REAL ESTATE CO., LTD.

00:38:31.847 --> 00:38:34.150
Is there something you want right now?

00:38:36.485 --> 00:38:38.988
-What?
-As of this moment. Anything?

00:38:48.864 --> 00:38:49.999
Where's my dad?

00:38:50.065 --> 00:38:51.467
He went to buy tea.

00:38:53.836 --> 00:38:55.438
What were you looking at?

00:38:55.504 --> 00:38:56.405
HOUSE FOR SALE

00:38:57.006 --> 00:38:57.873
A house?

00:39:03.846 --> 00:39:05.481
DRINKS CORNER

00:39:07.917 --> 00:39:09.185
42,500,000 YEN

00:39:16.792 --> 00:39:17.993
Welcome home!

00:39:20.663 --> 00:39:21.730
Dad, the tea?

00:39:25.835 --> 00:39:26.702
VANILLA ICE CREAM

00:39:27.503 --> 00:39:28.637
Where's the tea?

00:39:29.338 --> 00:39:30.773
This is in place of the tea.

00:39:31.674 --> 00:39:34.210
Ah, I only asked for two spoons.

00:39:35.277 --> 00:39:36.645
This spoon's from the other day.

00:39:37.613 --> 00:39:38.781
Here.

00:39:38.848 --> 00:39:40.316
We're eating straight from this?

00:39:42.718 --> 00:39:43.919
Uh…

00:39:52.328 --> 00:39:53.596
Okay then, let's dig in.

00:39:54.129 --> 00:39:55.197
Yeah.

00:40:04.006 --> 00:40:06.041
Well, okay.

00:40:16.919 --> 00:40:19.421
Let’s talk about our favorite ice cream.

00:40:20.689 --> 00:40:23.759
My favorite is the one
with ramune on the outside

00:40:23.826 --> 00:40:26.061
and vanilla on the inside.

00:40:26.128 --> 00:40:28.964
Refreshing and sweet. Best of both worlds.

00:40:30.165 --> 00:40:31.000
What about you?

00:40:33.435 --> 00:40:35.771
I'm the soft serve kind of person,
I suppose.

00:40:35.838 --> 00:40:38.207
The half chocolate, half vanilla kind?

00:40:38.707 --> 00:40:40.376
Just vanilla.

00:40:40.442 --> 00:40:41.443
No way.

00:40:41.944 --> 00:40:44.413
But the half-and-half ones
are the best deal!

00:40:46.482 --> 00:40:47.483
Yeah.

00:40:49.051 --> 00:40:51.453
What about you, Dad? What’s your favorite?

00:40:56.125 --> 00:40:57.626
Homerun Bars, I guess.

00:40:59.395 --> 00:41:01.363
The ice cream with a winning stick.

00:41:01.430 --> 00:41:02.264
That's cool.

00:41:04.066 --> 00:41:06.402
I used to eat those with him.

00:41:07.803 --> 00:41:09.905
The first guy I ever liked.

00:41:09.972 --> 00:41:11.206
What?

00:41:11.941 --> 00:41:13.876
We ate so many together,

00:41:13.943 --> 00:41:16.011
but I never once won.

00:41:17.479 --> 00:41:22.117
You know how people say it’s because
of karma, or you’ve done something wrong?

00:41:23.085 --> 00:41:25.187
I actually believed that.

00:41:27.556 --> 00:41:28.791
I thought the reason I didn’t win

00:41:29.992 --> 00:41:33.028
was because I liked a guy.

00:41:34.463 --> 00:41:35.831
That it was something wrong.

00:41:37.166 --> 00:41:39.368
So God wouldn’t let me win.

00:41:40.970 --> 00:41:41.870
I always

00:41:42.905 --> 00:41:44.640
felt out of place.

00:41:45.507 --> 00:41:49.345
That loving someone, dating,

00:41:49.411 --> 00:41:51.180
living together,

00:41:51.246 --> 00:41:54.516
and sharing ice cream were forbidden.

00:41:55.651 --> 00:41:58.120
Something I wasn’t allowed to want.

00:42:00.022 --> 00:42:01.690
I know that it's not true,

00:42:02.725 --> 00:42:06.095
but part of me still believes it.

00:42:13.068 --> 00:42:15.037
I’ve gotten used to giving up on things.

00:42:15.771 --> 00:42:19.174
But here we are,
eating ice cream together.

00:42:26.448 --> 00:42:29.652
If you don’t truly let yourself want
what you want, you’ll never have it.

00:42:33.455 --> 00:42:35.090
So, I’ve decided to let myself want it.

00:42:37.526 --> 00:42:38.861
You want a house?

00:42:38.927 --> 00:42:39.762
What?

00:42:46.235 --> 00:42:47.102
Yeah.

00:42:47.803 --> 00:42:48.871
I want a house.

00:42:49.371 --> 00:42:51.373
After the beep,

00:42:51.440 --> 00:42:54.109
please leave your name and message.

00:42:54.610 --> 00:42:55.878
Hello.

00:42:55.944 --> 00:42:57.680
So, the other day,

00:42:57.746 --> 00:42:59.114
someone new moved in.

00:43:00.683 --> 00:43:03.385
And for some reason,
he really wants a house.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:07.823
So, I thought about it too.
What do I want?

00:43:09.925 --> 00:43:12.761
I want everything that everyone else has.

00:43:14.830 --> 00:43:16.665
Ah! I'm such an idiot!

00:43:18.834 --> 00:43:20.269
Coming. Oh.

00:43:20.335 --> 00:43:21.403
I’m coming in for a bit.

00:43:21.470 --> 00:43:24.273
I might not get it,
but I want to give it a shot.

00:43:24.773 --> 00:43:26.075
Here…

00:43:27.543 --> 00:43:28.610
Huh?

00:43:29.411 --> 00:43:30.245
What the?

00:43:30.312 --> 00:43:32.481
-There’s 30 million yen in here.
-Thirty million?

00:43:33.549 --> 00:43:36.018
You want a house, right?

00:43:36.085 --> 00:43:39.254
I will buy you.

00:43:46.095 --> 00:43:47.429
SHIZUOKA'S SOUVENIRS

00:43:47.496 --> 00:43:48.597
‎Mom…

00:43:50.132 --> 00:43:51.800
Mom, is there something you want?

00:43:52.568 --> 00:43:53.902
What was it you wanted?

00:43:55.070 --> 00:43:57.339
Talk to you later, okay?

00:44:08.617 --> 00:44:09.685
I found it.

00:45:51.353 --> 00:45:53.222
Subtitle translation by: Jeffery